{"parse":{"title":"Geographical Range (Superseded)","pageid":3005,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Superseded by new definition from Guideline G1065\n</p><p><br>\n<b>2-1-245</b>\n</p><p>The maximum distance at which light from a light or other aid to navigation can reach an observer, as limited only by the curvature of the earth and refraction in the atmosphere and by the heights of the observer and of the light or aid.\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-image-border\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:Ch2_Fig9.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/9/9d/Ch2_Fig9.jpg/400px-Ch2_Fig9.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"143\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/9/9d/Ch2_Fig9.jpg/600px-Ch2_Fig9.jpg 1.5x, /wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/9/9d/Ch2_Fig9.jpg/800px-Ch2_Fig9.jpg 2x\"></a></span>\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/Geographical_Range\" title=\"Geographical Range\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260617082001\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.035 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.044 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 60/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 791/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 242/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   12.935      1 -total\n 74.68%    9.660      1 Template:Languages\n 50.08%    6.478      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n 24.35%    3.149      1 Template:IALAFooter\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:3005-0!canonical and timestamp 20260617082001 and revision id 8421. Rendering was triggered because: page-view\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Historic_Terms"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Alphabetical_Index"},{"sortkey":"","*":"IALA_Dictionary_1970-89_Edition"}]}}